John Christopher Meyer has obtained an MSci degree in Mathematical Sciences and a PhD in Applied Mathematics from the University of Birmingham. 
From the 20/21 academic cycle John has been the University of Birmingham's Head of Education for the Jinan University - University of Birmingham Joint Institute (J-BJI) located in Guangzhou, China, having previously served as CAA Lead for the (J-BJI).
John's research interests include mathematical analysis, applied mathematics, and mathematics education (with CAA a particular area of interest).
